Bob Hope will pay tribute to Lucille Ball on Saturday with a special "Bob Hope's Love 
Affair With Lucille Ball."  Hope keeps voluminous files where Ball first appears in 1945 
on a show for charity called "G.I. Journal."  They then were in four movies together and 
often appeared on each other's radio and TV shows.  Their last performance together was 
the March Academy Awards ceremony.  Hope also remembers hiring her first husband 
Desi Arnaz 50 years ago.  The special will include special guest stars and clips from their 
appearances together, which Hope personally selected from his archives.</SUM>  
